HEADWORD: Outact
<hw>Out*act"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To do or beyond;
to exceed in acting.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He has made me heir to treasures⟦br⟧
Would make me <qex>outact</qex> a real window's whining.</q>
<rj><qau>Otway.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outagamies</ent>⟦br⟧
